            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["dashboard","quiz"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"passingScore":80,"questionsPerQuiz":8,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"db1","text":"You log in to QB Engineer and see a loading overlay before the Dashboard appears. Why does the Dashboard load this way?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The Dashboard is slow because it renders 3D graphics"},{"id":"b","text":"It uses a global loading overlay because it fetches data from multiple endpoints simultaneously — all widgets load together behind the overlay","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Each widget loads independently with its own spinner"},{"id":"d","text":"The loading overlay is a bug — the Dashboard should load instantly from cache"}],"explanation":"The Dashboard uses LoadingService (global overlay) because it fetches data from multiple API endpoints at once. The overlay clears when all data is ready, so you see the complete dashboard without partial loading or flickering."},{"id":"db2","text":"You see a job highlighted in red in the Today's Tasks widget. What does this mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job has been flagged as high priority by a manager"},{"id":"b","text":"The job's due date has passed — it's overdue","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The job is blocked by a hold and cannot proceed"},{"id":"d","text":"The job was recently assigned to you and hasn't been viewed yet"}],"explanation":"Overdue jobs (past their due date) are highlighted with red/error coloring in the Today's Tasks widget so they stand out from upcoming tasks and get immediate attention."},{"id":"db3","text":"You rearrange your Dashboard widgets by dragging them to new positions. What happens to your layout?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It resets to default when you refresh the page"},{"id":"b","text":"It's saved to your user preferences and persists across sessions and devices","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It's only saved in the current browser tab"},{"id":"d","text":"You need to click a Save Layout button to persist changes"}],"explanation":"Widget positions are saved automatically to user preferences (localStorage + API). Your layout is restored when you log in from any device — no manual save needed."},{"id":"db4","text":"The Cycle Progress widget's status chip has turned red and reads 'Overdue'. What does this indicate?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The planning cycle has been paused by an admin"},{"id":"b","text":"Every entry in the cycle is now complete"},{"id":"c","text":"The cycle is past its end date — you're behind schedule with work still outstanding","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"The widget failed to load and is showing an error state"}],"explanation":"The Cycle Progress widget's status chip normally counts down the days remaining in the cycle. Once the cycle runs past its end date it switches to a red 'Overdue' label — a cue that the cycle is behind schedule. (The progress fill itself is teal and only turns green at 100%; it never turns red or yellow.)"},{"id":"db5","text":"You want to record your Top 3 priorities for tomorrow from the Dashboard. How?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Navigate to the Planning page and add them to the next cycle"},{"id":"b","text":"Type them into the End of Day widget's textarea and click Save","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"They are generated automatically — you can't enter them yourself"},{"id":"d","text":"You can only enter them from the job's detail panel"}],"explanation":"The End of Day widget prompts you to capture your Top 3 for tomorrow. Type them into the textarea and click Save; the widget then shows your saved response with an Edit button to revise it later."},{"id":"db6","text":"You click a job in the Today's Tasks widget. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job's Kanban card is highlighted on the board"},{"id":"b","text":"The job detail dialog opens, showing subtasks, files, activity log, and available actions","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"A summary tooltip appears with the job title and due date"},{"id":"d","text":"You're navigated to the Backlog page with that job selected"}],"explanation":"Clicking a job in Today's Tasks opens the full job detail dialog. From there you can view and manage subtasks, files, activity history, and take actions like updating status."},{"id":"db7","text":"A new employee logs in and sees a 'Getting Started' banner on their Dashboard. When does this banner disappear?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"After 7 days, regardless of progress"},{"id":"b","text":"Only after every onboarding step shows a checkmark"},{"id":"c","text":"When enough onboarding steps are complete — like creating a job, adding a customer, and setting up track types — or when the employee dismisses it with the close button","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"It never disappears — it transforms into a regular widget"}],"explanation":"The Getting Started banner tracks setup steps (create your first job, add a customer, set up track types, receive first stock, explore reports — filtered to the modules your install has enabled). It hides automatically once enough steps are complete, and you can also dismiss it manually with the close button."},{"id":"db8","text":"You glance at the Jobs by Stage widget. What does the length of each bar represent?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"How long jobs have been sitting in that stage"},{"id":"b","text":"The number of jobs in that stage, scaled against the busiest stage","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The total dollar value of jobs in that stage"},{"id":"d","text":"How overdue the jobs in that stage are"}],"explanation":"The Jobs by Stage widget draws one bar per board stage, with each bar's length proportional to that stage's job count relative to the busiest stage. The count is also shown numerically beside each bar."},{"id":"db9","text":"The Inventory Snapshot widget shows a non-zero low-stock count highlighted in alert color. What is it telling you?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"That many parts are missing a description"},{"id":"b","text":"That some parts have dropped to or below their minimum stock threshold","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"That inventory counts haven't been reconciled this month"},{"id":"d","text":"That new stock has just been received"}],"explanation":"The Inventory Snapshot widget shows part count, total on-hand, and a low-stock count. When parts fall to or below their minimum threshold, the low-stock figure is highlighted and the affected parts are listed with their current vs minimum quantities."},{"id":"db10","text":"How are jobs ordered in the Today's Tasks widget?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Alphabetically by job title"},{"id":"b","text":"By status priority — overdue first, then active, upcoming, and completed","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"By creation date — newest first"},{"id":"d","text":"Randomly each time the page loads"}],"explanation":"Today's Tasks orders jobs by their status: overdue items come first so they get immediate attention, followed by active, upcoming, and completed. The widget shows the top several and surfaces an overdue alert banner when any are past due."},{"id":"db11","text":"You want to see how many sales orders are currently in production. Where do you look on the Dashboard?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The KPI chips at the top of the page"},{"id":"b","text":"The Open Orders widget — it breaks the open-order total down by Confirmed, In Production, and Partially Shipped","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The Today's Tasks widget — count the items manually"},{"id":"d","text":"The Cycle Progress widget — it breaks down by stage"}],"explanation":"The Open Orders widget shows the total open sales orders plus a breakdown by Confirmed, In Production, and Partially Shipped. Look at the In Production count for your answer."},{"id":"db12","text":"The Action Items widget lists a follow-up task. What two quick actions can you take on it directly from the widget?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Reassign it or change its priority"},{"id":"b","text":"Complete it (check) or dismiss it (close)","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Print it or export it to PDF"},{"id":"d","text":"Snooze it or escalate it to a manager"}],"explanation":"Each Action Items row has a check button to complete the task and a close button to dismiss it, so you can clear follow-ups without leaving the dashboard. When the list is empty the widget shows an empty state."}]}"""
        });

        // ── Customizing Your Dashboard (Walkthrough) ─────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Customizing Your Dashboard",
            Slug = "dashboard-customize-walkthrough",
            Summary = "Enter edit mode to add, remove, rearrange, and resize widgets — and reset the whole layout back to defaults.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Walkthrough,
            EstimatedMinutes = 5,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 5,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["dashboard","widgets","customize","layout"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"appRoute":"/dashboard","startButtonLabel":"Customize Dashboard","steps":[{"element":".page-header__actions","popover":{"title":"Dashboard Controls","description":"Every dashboard control lives in the page header: Focus Mode, Ambient, Export, and Customize. Customizing your layout always starts here — the dashboard is read-only until you turn on edit mode.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".page-header__actions .btn:last-child","popover":{"title":"Click Customize to Edit","description":"This is the Customize button. Click it to enter edit mode — the icon flips to a check and the button highlights. Edit mode is REQUIRED before you can drag, resize, add, or remove widgets; outside edit mode the grid is locked so you never disturb your layout by accident. Click it again (now labeled 'Done') to leave edit mode and save.","side":"bottom"}},{"element":".dashboard-content","popover":{"title":"Drag and Resize in Edit Mode","description":"Once edit mode is on, an edit bar appears above the grid and each widget gains a drag handle and resize grips. Grab a widget by its header to move it, or drag its lower-right corner to resize. The grid snaps widgets into place, and every change is saved to your user preferences automatically — your layout is restored next login from any device.","side":"top"}},{"element":".page-header__actions","popover":{"title":"Add Widget, Remove, and Reset","description":"In edit mode the edit bar gives you 'Add Widget' (a menu of every widget not already on your dashboard — filtered to the modules your install has enabled) and 'Reset', which restores the default widget set and arrangement. Each widget also shows a small X in its corner to remove it. Removing a widget just hides it; you can add it back any time from the Add Widget menu.","side":"bottom"}}]}"""
        });

        // ── Dashboard Display Modes (Article) ────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Dashboard Display Modes — Focus & Ambient",
            Slug = "dashboard-display-modes",
            Summary = "Focus Mode strips the dashboard down to just your tasks and orders; Ambient Mode turns it into a full-screen status display. How to enter, exit, and what persists.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 6,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["dashboard","focus-mode","ambient-mode","display"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Dashboard Display Modes\n\nBeyond the standard widget grid, the Dashboard offers two alternate display modes — **Focus Mode** and **Ambient Mode**. Both are toggled from buttons in the dashboard header, and each serves a different need.\n\n### Focus Mode\n\nFocus Mode strips the dashboard down to the three things you act on personally: **My Tasks**, **Open Orders**, and the **End of Day** prompt. Everything else — KPI chips, charts, team load — is hidden so you can concentrate on your own work without distraction.\n\n**Entering and exiting:** Click the **Focus Mode** button in the header (the crosshair / `center_focus_strong` icon). The button highlights while Focus Mode is active. Click it again, or use the close (X) button inside the focus panel, to return to the full dashboard.\n\n**It lives in the URL.** Turning on Focus Mode adds `?focus=true` to the page URL. That means the mode is bookmarkable and shareable — you can save a direct link that always opens straight into Focus Mode, and a browser refresh keeps you there. Your choice is also saved to your user preferences, so the dashboard remembers your last setting.\n\n**Mutually exclusive with Ambient.** Focus Mode and Ambient Mode can't both be on at once — entering Focus Mode automatically exits Ambient Mode.\n\n### Ambient Mode\n\nAmbient Mode turns the dashboard into a full-screen, glanceable status display: a large clock and date, headline KPIs (active jobs, overdue, hours today), and a short list of upcoming deadlines. It's designed for a wall-mounted monitor or a screen you walk past — readable from across the room, with no controls to fiddle with.\n\n**Entering manually:** Click the **Ambient** button in the header (the `nightlight` icon).\n\n**Entering automatically (auto-idle):** The dashboard also drops into Ambient Mode on its own after a period of inactivity. The idle timeout is configurable; auto-ambient is suppressed while you're editing the layout or already in Focus Mode, so it never interrupts deliberate work.\n\n**Exiting:** Ambient Mode is meant to be dismissed instantly — press **Escape**, or simply click anywhere on the screen, and you're back to the normal dashboard. A hint at the bottom of the ambient display reminds you of this.\n\n**Live data.** While ambient, the display keeps itself current: the clock ticks every second and the KPIs/deadlines refresh in the background, so a wall display never goes stale.\n\n### Which to use when\n\n- **Heads-down on your own work?** Focus Mode — fewer widgets, just your tasks, orders, and end-of-day note.\n- **Driving a shared/wall monitor, or stepping away?** Ambient Mode — big clock, headline numbers, deadlines, dismiss with a tap or Escape.\n- **Day-to-day operating?** The standard widget grid, which you can tailor with the Customize controls.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        // ── Dashboard Widgets Catalog (QuickRef) ─────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
